# BD Bible Policy System - Claude Rules

## Project Overview
This is the RPRC Business Development Bible Policy System, implementing capture and proposal management workflows.

## Brand Standards
ALL colors MUST follow GMU (George Mason University) official brand guidelines:
- Primary Green: #006633
- Primary Gold: #FFCC33
- Dark Green: #00563F
- Secondary Gold: #FFB81C
- White: #FFFFFF
- Light Gray: #F5F5F5

No other colors should be used without explicit approval.

## Code Standards
1. All React components use functional components with hooks
2. Styling uses inline styles with GMU colors from gmuTheme.js
3. Components should be modular and reusable
4. Error handling: use optional chaining (?.) and default values

## File Structure
src/
├── components/        # Reusable components
├── App.js            # Main application
├── gmuTheme.js       # GMU color theme
└── [feature].js      # Feature components

## Component Guidelines
- Always import gmuColors from './gmuTheme'
- Use consistent naming: RPRCCaptureDashboard, QuadChart, etc.
- Props should have default values to prevent errors
- Documents prop should always use: documents = [] or documents?.length || 0

## Business Logic
Follow RPRC's documented processes:
1. Capture Process (Chas's document) - 4 gates
2. Proposal Workflow (Jen Namvar's document) - Color team reviews
3. All processes must align with these source documents

## When Making Changes
1. Maintain GMU colors throughout
2. Test all navigation buttons work
3. Ensure no undefined errors (use optional chaining)
4. Keep components modular
5. Follow existing patterns
